{{Sufism}} '''Baba Kuhi of Shiraz''' (948 - 1037 CE) was a 10th- and 11th-century Persian<ref>Craig A. Lockard. Societies, Networks, and Transitions, Volume I: To 1500: A Global History. — 3. — Cengage Learning, 2014. — P. 230</ref> [[Sufi]] mystic. Probably born in [[Shiraz]] (now in Southern Iran). As a young man he met the Arab poet [[Al-Mutanabbi]] and the well-known Sufi Abū ʿAbdallāh Moḥammad.<ref name=encyciran>[http://www.iranicaonline.org/articles/baba-kuhi BĀBĀ KUHI] at Encyclopedia Iranica</ref>
