In [[Gnosticism]] '''Hystereme''' is the [[world of deficiency]].<ref name="Goodrick-ClarkeGoodrick-Clarke2005">{{cite book|author1=Nicholas Goodrick-Clarke|author2=Clare Goodrick-Clarke|title=G.R.S. Mead and the Gnostic Quest|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=CwKkFAWtimoC&pg=PA67|year=2005|publisher=North Atlantic Books|isbn=978-1-55643-572-0|page=67}}</ref><ref name="Exeter2008">{{cite book|author=Nicholas Goodrick-Clarke Chair of Western Esotericism and Director of the Centre for the Study of Western Esotericism University of Exeter|title=The Western Esoteric Traditions : A Historical Introduction: A Historical Introduction|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=IPwoK5XYXrAC&pg=PA27|date=16 September 2008|publisher=Oxford University Press, USA|isbn=978-0-19-971756-9|page=27}}</ref>

